metadata.name: Complete SEL Setup
metadata.description:
Fully configured setup based on Tamtaro's recommended filters, sort orders, and Standard SEL described on the [github](https://github.com/Tam-Taro/SEL-Filtering-and-Sorting). Designed for those with debrid or usenet services, while seeking the highest quality results, minimal clutter, and complete coverage even when options are few. 

 * Comes with addons and formatter. Use my other templates to keep your existing addons/formatter. 
 * Standard SEL keeps around 20 results. Import Extended SEL Only template afterwards to keep 2x more. Github has more SEL options to try out. 
 * **â“˜ For catalogs, check out Github for AIOMetadata configs.**
 * Review the Language filter. Add your main languages to Preferred Languages, keep rest the same. 
 * Some addons are included but disabled; just turn them on if you use them (eg. Torbox). 
 * Comes with auto-synced urls for [Vidhin's Regexes](https://github.com/Vidhin05/Releases-Regex) to score & tag streams with my custom Formatter.
metadata.author: Tamtaro

metadata.name: Extended SEL Only Template
metadata.description: This template includes a modified version of the Standard SEL in the Complete SEL Setup to show twice as many results. It will import all my synced URLs for Excluded + Included + Preferred Stream Expressions, so everything on Stream Expressions page except Ranked Stream Expressions. Nothing else will get overridden in your setup. To make use of the Preferred Stream Expressions, you will need to add Stream Expressions Matched into your Sort Order. Check out some optional SELs on [Github](https://github.com/Tam-Taro/SEL-Filtering-and-Sorting) for you to try. The Extended SEL comes with multiple lines that smartly filter your results when necessary so that your final result page has a complete coverage of quality streams and minimal clutter. Around 40 streams should remain after filtering on average, depending on your source availability.

metadata.name: Standard SEL Only Template
metadata.description: This template has only the Standard SEL used in the Complete SEL Setup. It will import all my synced URLs for Excluded + Included + Preferred Stream Expressions, so everything on Stream Expressions page except Ranked Stream Expressions. Read up on [Github](https://github.com/Tam-Taro/SEL-Filtering-and-Sorting) for more info & optional SELs to try. Nothing else will get overridden in your setup. To make use of the Preferred Stream Expressions, you will need to add Stream Expressions Matched into your Sort Order. The SEL template comes with multiple lines that smartly filter your results when necessary so that your final result page has a complete coverage of quality streams and minimal clutter. Around 20 streams should remain after filtering on average, depending on your source availability. Check out Extended SEL Only Template if you want to keep 2x more.
